Tristen</FONT><FORM method=post action="http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.processVote?topicID=207.topic"><table border=0 cellpadding=3 cellspacing=0 width="55%"><tbody><tr><td><input type="radio" name="choice" value="1"><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Just because you have a DOT on you doesn't mean your in combat.</FONT></td></tr><tr><td><input type="radio" name="choice" value="2"><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>If you taking hits, you in combat.</FONT></td></tr><tr><td><input type="radio" name="choice" value="3"><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>I dont' know what your taking about.</FONT></td></tr><tr><td><input type="radio" name="choice" value="4"><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Speed classes are Umber and the only way to kill one is to DOT and wack!</FONT></td></tr></tbody></table><P><input type=submit value="Vote"><a HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showMessage?topicID=207.topic&pollResults=on><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Show results</FONT></A> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uskippydedooda.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Skippy Dedooda</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/25/02 8:31:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=207.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.mrcrazysurfer.com/skippy/msgboard/personal.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Should DOTs break Speed?</span><hr size=1> technically when singing, you are channeling the power of your god through you..... so it would make sense to lose the speed, or actually even other songs from a pure roleplaying sense.<br>
not trying to flame here, just saying I  think not enough people can just appreciate something for what it is, they need to try to force it to fit into their liking.<br>
So on that note, I want everyone to start paying homage to Skippy because I don't like the way things are now, I only ask 3% of your income, most churchs ask for 10% tithing. Nerf your salary. I don't think we executives make nearly enough for what we do. Nerf car speed, there is no reason to tear through a neighborhood at 60 in your little sportscar because it will corner ok, because when you take that corner at 60 you end up with someone's kid glued to your front bumper. Nerf the media, because they keep trying to park in my driveway whenever there is news at the local shipyard. Nerf everything but DAMN leave a game alone already. something with fixed rules and an ability to expect certain things to happen within the confines of the game and everyone wants to change it.<br>
