<br>
It's not fair to lump all stealth classes together like that I think.  They are VERY different, and it would be online with saying all Casting classes....   I understand your frustration, but I don't agree with that line.<br>
<br>
As a skald who used to play a hunter before they got nerfed into utter pieces of crap, I can tell you that it's easy to find a stealther once they have stealthed.<br>
<br>
First you have to understand how stealth works.   Based on skill, when a person gets into the stealthers radius that they &quot;could&quot; see them,  a timer starts ticking down.  IF you are still in the stealthers radius when that timer expires they will become visible.   A skalds biggest problem is they we just love to run so damn fast around that we run in and out of that radius before it expires looking for one.<br>
<br>
It also helps to have an assassin who has see hidden and the RA ability to do so as well.   Then they(your assassin buddy) can see the schmuck running very slowly away and with skald speed run over to him/her/it and smack it!  Soon as thats done you just lay waste to em.<br>
<br>
Another thing is that you have to be out of combat for 10 seconds to restealth.   IF you get the jump on the &quot;stealther&quot; who then tries to run away, do NOT blow the wad with both DDs on them trying to kill them quickly.  I use swinging and 1 DD as a killing,  and the other DD I usally leave open that I can use to make sure the person gets hit atleast every 10 seconds so they can't restealth.   This is only when they are running tho.   <br>
<br>
<br>
And yes I agree that DoT does NOT mean your in combat and shouldn't stop our run speed.    If a person doesn't LIKE that our speed can kick in, they just have to swing at us again as we try to run away from them.<br>
<br>
<br>
Ed<br>
